  "A data set of 12 home prices (in thousands) sorted in order is: 150, 175, 190, 210, 225, 240, 255, 270, 290, 310, 350, 400. Find Q1, Q3, and the IQR.": "",
  "Q1 = 210, Q3 = 290, IQR = 80": "",
  "Q1 = 190, Q3 = 310, IQR = 120": "",
  "Q1 = 200, Q3 = 300, IQR = 100": "",
  "Q1 = 175, Q3 = 350, IQR = 175": "",
  "Lower half: {150,175,190,210,225,240}. Q1 = (190+210)/2 = 200. Upper half: {255,270,290,310,350,400}. Q3 = (290+310)/2 = 300. IQR = 300−200 = 100.": "",
  "Using the home price data from the previous question (Q1=200, Q3=300, IQR=100), determine the outlier fences. Is the $400k home an outlier?": "",
  "Lower fence = 200, Upper fence = 300; $400k IS an outlier": "",
  "There are no outlier fences for this data": "",
  "Lower fence = 50, Upper fence = 450; $400k is NOT an outlier": "",
  "Lower fence = 100, Upper fence = 400; $400k IS an outlier": "",
  "Lower fence = Q1 − 1.5×IQR = 200 − 150 = 50. Upper fence = Q3 + 1.5×IQR = 300 + 150 = 450. Since 400 < 450, the $400k home is not an outlier.": "",
