  "A fitness test records push-up counts for 20 recruits. The sorted data yields Q1 = 22, Median = 30, Q3 = 38. A recruit does 55 push-ups. The drill sergeant says this is an 'extreme outlier.' Using the 3×IQR rule for extreme outliers, is the sergeant correct?": "",
